E2E Scenario: Successful Login, Product Verification, Add to Cart, and Logout

Description:
Verify that a user can log in successfully, view products, add a product to the cart, and log out of the SauceDemo application.

Pre-conditions:

The user has valid credentials.

The SauceDemo application is accessible.

The user is on the login page: https://www.saucedemo.com/

Test Steps:

Open the browser and navigate to https://www.saucedemo.com/

Enter standard_user in the Username field.

Enter secret_sauce in the Password field.

Click the Login button.

Verify the Products page is displayed.

Select any product (e.g., Sauce Labs Backpack).

Click Add to Cart for the selected product.

Verify the cart badge shows 1 item.

Click the Shopping Cart icon.

Verify the selected product appears in the cart.

Click the Menu (â˜°) button.

Click Logout.

Expected Result:

The user is redirected to the inventory page after login.

Product list is displayed correctly.

Selected product is added to the cart successfully.

Cart reflects the correct item count.

The user is logged out successfully and redirected to the login page.

Post-conditions:

The user session is terminated.

No active login remains.